06:02.029 --> 06:04.823
<i>no matter how wild
they might seem at the time.</i>

06:47.991 --> 06:49.284
Hey!

07:04.007 --> 07:06.552
Of course! That's it.

07:06.635 --> 07:09.388
If we could send a craft
to orbit the asteroid,

07:09.471 --> 07:13.141
then we could use the grabbing action
of a robot arm to get a sample.

07:13.225 --> 07:16.895
We don't need the whole asteroid.
We could study a piece of it.

07:16.979 --> 07:19.147
<i>That's a great idea, Franklin.</i>

07:19.773 --> 07:20.816
Really?

07:20.899 --> 07:23.944
<i>It'll take some time
to organize the logistics,</i>

07:24.027 --> 07:27.781
<i>but I'd say you've come up with
a fantastic plan.</i>

07:27.865 --> 07:31.159
<i>NASA will definitely be
putting this mission into place.</i>

07:31.243 --> 07:33.996
<i>What a terrific way to end the day.</i>

07:34.079 --> 07:35.664
Yeehaw!

07:38.375 --> 07:40.419
Thanks for the idea, Snoopy.
